summary: Ever got annoyed by the creaking sound skeletons make when they're doing absolutely nothing but standing around? Then you could try these modified idle sounds. No esp, just two replacer audio files.
descriptionHtml:
[font=Comic Sans MS][size=5][b][u]WHAT IS THIS?[/u]
[/b][/size][/font]
These are two [b]modified vanilla sound files[/b] which [b]replace[/b] the skeletons' creaking sounds.
No esp involved.

Click this link to listen to a sample (recorded in game): [b][size=3][url=https://instaud.io/zQq]Audio Sample
[/url][/size][/b]
It's basically the same vanilla creaking sound, but the pitch of the two sounds is now different from each other, and generally lower, to give it some more variety. Also the underlying breathing sound has been amplified, some parts were cut out to create a pause between inhaling and exhaling (yeah, I know, skeletons don't breathe - go tell Beth), and the whole thing is a bit quieter than before, and thus a bit less intrusive.





[size=5][b][u][font=Comic Sans MS]INSTALLATION[/font][/u][/b][/size]

[size=3][b]To install, copy the contents of the "Quieter Skeletons" folder into your Skyrim main folder.

To uninstall, delete "npc_skeleton_conscious_01_lp.wav" and "npc_skeleton_conscious_02_lp.wav"
in "data/sound/fx/npc/skeleton/"[/b][/size]

[size=1](NOTE: You CAN listen to the downloaded wavs by opening them with your preferred player, but you SHOULDN'T decide anything based on the impression you get by doing this. Why, you ask? Because what you will hear is usually very different from what you hear in game. That's because of how the game handles sounds and applies additional effects on them. This is true for (almost) all sound files you get from mods.)[/size]





[font=Comic Sans MS][size=5][u][b]COMPATIBILITY[/b][/u][/size][/font]

Not compatible with mods that have their own versions of "npc_skeleton_conscious_01_lp.wav" and "npc_skeleton_conscious_02_lp.wav", but doesn't break anything.





[font=Comic Sans MS][size=5][u][b]CREDITS[/b][/u][/size][/font]

Bethesda - The guy (or girl) there who made the original skeleton sounds.
